#EXTM3U
# ============================================================================
#  SabiStream — combined demo playlist  (Live TV + Movies + Series)
# ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#  Built for Google Play review / closed testing. Copyright-safe: contains ONLY
#  Creative Commons open movies (Blender Foundation — Big Buck Bunny, Sintel,
#  Tears of Steel, Elephants Dream; CC BY 3.0, www.blender.org) and public
#  developer test streams (Apple, Mux, Amazon CloudFront, and Google's sample
#  MP4 bucket). No paid TV, no broadcast/cable rebroadcast, no PPV, no sports.
#
#  HOW THE THREE TABS GET POPULATED  (SabiStream classifies a plain M3U by the
#  URL + name, NOT by the group name):
#    • Live TV — live HLS streams (.m3u8). group-title -> the Live category.
#    • Movies  — direct video files (.mp4) with no episode tag.
#                group-title -> the Movie category.
#    • Series  — .mp4 files whose NAME carries an episode tag like S01E01.
#                Episodes group by the show title (the text BEFORE the SxxEyy
#                token); the season comes from the Sxx number.
#
#  WHY THE MOVIES BELOW USE .mp4 AND NOT .m3u8: an entry whose GROUP is "Movies"
#  but is served as a live .m3u8 stream is filed under LIVE on purpose, so that
#  a genuine live "Movies 24" TV channel never gets mis-sorted into the Movies
#  tab. On-demand content therefore has to look on-demand (a real file URL, or a
#  /movie//series/ path), which is what a real IPTV panel's M3U export also does.
# ============================================================================


# ─────────────────────────────── LIVE TV ───────────────────────────────────
# Category: "Demo Live"
#EXTINF:-1 tvg-id="demo.live.apple1" tvg-logo="https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/fa/Apple_logo_black.svg" group-title="Demo Live",Apple Test Channel HD
